    "body": "### Problem\n\nHaving slow internet connection and installing plugins via vim.pack can result in a timeout\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/41935306-ff66-40d9-8194-bf39d3adf993\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ninit.lua\n```lua\nvim.pack.add({\n\t\"https://github.com/seblyng/nvim-ts-autotag\",\n\t\"https://github.com/seblyng/roslyn.nvim\",\n\t\"https://github.com/mason-org/mason.nvim\",\n\t{ src = \"https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter\", version = \"main\" },\n\t\"https://github.com/github/copilot.vim\",\n\t\"https://github.com/seblyng/git-conflict.nvim\",\n\t\"https://github.com/nvim-tree/nvim-web-devicons\",\n\t\"https://github.com/Bekaboo/dropbar.nvim\",\n\t\"https://github.com/j-hui/fidget.nvim\",\n\t\"https://github.com/iamcco/markdown-preview.nvim\",\n\t\"https://github.com/nvim-lua/plenary.nvim\",\n\t\"https://github.com/olimorris/codecompanion.nvim\",\n\t\"https://github.com/mfussenegger/nvim-dap\",\n})\n```\n\nHave slow internet connection and try to install plugins. Times out if it takes ~30 seconds.\nI am using the init.lua above.\n\nInteresting is that using the commit from when vim.pack was introduced does not lead to a timeout. Indicating to me that it was maybe a couple of seconds faster previously. I tried to bisect to find some pointers on where it slowed down a bit, but it is a bit hard when the network suddenly decides to speed up making it not time out.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect the timeout for `async.run(joined_f):wait()` to be larger than the default timeout in `vim._async` which seems to be 30 seconds. \n\nBriefly looking at other package managers it seems like:\n- lazy.nvim: 2 minutes\n- pckr.nvim: 1 minute\n- mini.deps: 30 seconds (this is 30 seconds per clone, so not exactly the same as vim.pack if I understand it correctly)\n\nWhat about increasing the timeout to 1 or 2 minutes?\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1427+gc9b74f8b7e\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.0.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.2.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild",
