            "body": "> I would expect the timeout for `async.run(joined_f):wait()` to be larger than the default timeout in `vim._async` which seems to be 30 seconds.\n\nWe also need to make sure that CTRL-c will cancel the job. #7546 #7546 I wonder if CTRL-c could trigger a `Progress` callback, so that `Progress` consumers (such as `vim.pack`) can handle cancellation.\n",
