            "body": "> * mini.deps: 30 seconds (this is 30 seconds per clone, so not exactly the same as vim.pack if I understand it correctly)\n\nThe timeout in `vim.pack` comes solely from `vim._async` and its `:wait()` method. It is used [here in `vim.pack`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/b459bf5961fd6bbd7c887d9c3751ff5dbbdcf55d/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua#L472-L476), which I'd guess acts as a timeout for the joined function, i.e. indeed waits 30 second for *all* jobs to complete. @lewis6991, is my understanding here correct?\n\n@justinmk, configurable timeout exactly for this case is one of the value propositions of `vim.pack.config()` (#34772).",
